The verdict is not yet final, and the appeal of the convicts is due to be heard in December.
Tymoshenko himself calls the verdict political revenge by the regime and the trial has also raised suspicions in the West of the court's bias.
The motion, Article 365, on the basis of which the former Prime Minister was convicted, to remove her from the Penal Code was supported by 147 MPs.
226 votes would have been needed to pass it.
