The beginning of a new crisis
France and the rest of Europe in the focus of investors.
On Tuesday, a statistical storm broke through Europe.
The countries published their GDP figures for the third quarter.
The Czech economy stagnated compared with the previous quarter, with Germany and France growing.
The bond market is now breaking all records.
The investors are not only looking at Greece, but also at Spain, France, Austria and other countries.
The statistical offices of the Euro­zone, Germany, the Czech Republic and a number of other European countries have published their preliminary forecasts for the third quarter.
Germany's GDP was expected to grow by 0.5% and France's by 0.4%.
